vy.%3Cp%3ETalia%20Lakritz%2FBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201945%2C%20a%20Japanese%20submarine%20fired%20torpedoes%20at%20the%20Indianapolis%20as%20it%20traveled%20from%20Guam%20to%20Leyte%20after%20delivering%20the%20atomic%20bomb%20that%20would%20later%20be%20used%20on%20Hiroshima.%20The%20ship%20sank%2012%20minutes%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOut%20of%201%2C195%20crew%20members%2C%20316%20survived%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usni.org%2Fmagazines%2Fnaval-history-magazine%2F2021%2Foctober%2Flessons-accountability-charles-mcvay-and-indianapolis%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Naval%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Around%20200%20crew%20members%20reportedly%20died%20from%20shark%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ship%20became%20more%20well-known%20after%20its%20mention%20in%20the%20movie%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteven-spielberg-jaws-shocked-hit-shark-looked-dumb-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJaws%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20the%20character%20Quint%20recounts%20his%20experience%20as%20a%20survivor%20of%20the%20Indianapolis%20wreck%20and%20the%20gruesome%20shark%20attacks%20that%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcVay%20was%20the%20only%20Navy%20commander%20to%20be%20court-martialed%20for%20losing%20a%20ship%20during%20battle%20in%20World%20War%20II.%20He%20was%20widely%20viewed%20as%20a%20scapegoat%2C%20leading%20his%20conviction%20to%20be%20overturned%20by%20Navy%20Secretary%20James%20Forrestal%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2001%2F07%2F14%2Fus%2Fcaptain-once-a-scapegoat-is-absolved.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20Still%2C%20his%20reputation%20never%20truly%20recovered.%20He%20died%20by%20suicide%20in%201968%2C%20and%20over%2050%20years%20later%2C%20Congress%20passed%20a%20resolution%20fully%20exonerating%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv