lor-swift-concert-a-selfie-follows%2Farticleshow%2F111191948.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fwatch-prince-william-shakes-it-off-at-taylor-swift-concert-a-selfie-follows%2Famp_articleshow%2F111191948.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fuk%2Fwatch-prince-william-shakes-it-off-at-taylor-swift-concert-a-selfie-follows%2Famp_articleshow%2F111191948.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Find%20Out%20Which%20ITR%20Form%20Is%20Required%20For%20Your%20Income%20Tax%20Filing%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFiling%20your%20ITR%20is%20not%20just%20important%20but%20also%20a%20legal%20requirement.%20It%20provides%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Department%20with%20details%20about%20your%20income%20and%20taxes%20paid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20date%20to%20submit%20your%20Income%20Tax%20Return%20(ITR)%20for%20the%20assessment%20year%202024-25%20in%20India%20is%20July%2031%2C%202024.%20If%20you%20file%20after%20this%20date%2C%20you'll%20incur%20a%20late%20fee%20of%20Rs.%20500%20per%20month%20or%20part%20thereof%2C%20up%20to%20a%20maximum%20of%20Rs.%201%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20mandatory%20to%20file%20an%20ITR%20if%20you%20earned%20income%20from%20or%20invested%20in%20foreign%20assets%20during%20the%20financial%20year.%20When%20applying%20for%20visas%20or%20loans%2C%20having%20an%20ITR%20filed%20is%20crucial.%20Whether%20your%20business%20made%20a%20profit%20or%20incurred%20losses%2C%20filing%20your%20ITR%20is%20a%20legal%20obligation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20experienced%20business%20losses%20or%20undercapital%20gains%2C%20you%20can%20only%20carry%20them%20forward%20to%20the%20next%20year%20if%20you%20file%20your%20return%20before%20the%20due%20date.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.incometax.gov.in%2Fiec%2Ffoportal%2Fhelp%2Fidentification-and-generation-of-applicable-itr-individual-faq%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHelp%20me%20decide%20which%20ITR%20form%20to%20file%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20Financial%20Year%20(FY)%202023-24%2C%20which%20corresponds%20to%20the%20Assessment%20Year%20(AY)%202024-25%2C%20the%20type%20of%20Income%20Tax%20Return%20(ITR)%20form%20that%20should%20be%20filed%20depends%20on%20the%20nature%20of%20your%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere%20are%20the%20common%20ITR%20forms%20used%20for%20individuals%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EITR-1%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20also%20known%20as%20Sahaj%2C%20is%20a%20simplified%20Income%20Tax%20Return%20form%20intended%20for%20resident%20individuals%20with%20a%20total%20annual%20income%20of%20up%20to%20Rs.%2050%20lakh.%20It%20is%20suitable%20for%20individuals%20who%20earn%20income%20from%20sources%20such%20as%20salary%2C%20pension%2C%20one-house%20property%2C%20or%20other%20sources%20(excluding%20specific%20categories).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EITR-2%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20an%20extensive%20income%20tax%20return%20form%20for%20individuals%20and%20HUFs.%20It%20applies%20to%20those%20with%20diverse%20income%20sources%2C%20including%20income%20from%20capital%20gains%2C%20foreign%20income%2C%20or%20agricultural%20income%20over%20Rs.%205%2C000.%20Eligible%20individuals%20include%20directors%20of%20companies%2C%20residents%20not%20ordinarily%20resident%20(RNOR)%2C%20or%20non-residents.%20It%20also%20covers%20those%20with%20investments%20in%20unlisted%20equity%2C%20assets%20abroad%2C%20or%20obligations%20like%20tax%20under%20Section%20194N%20or%20ESOPs%2C%20and%20allows%20for%20carrying%20forward%20losses%20from%20previous%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EITR-3%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20tailored%20for%20individuals%20and%20Hindu%20Undivided%20Families%20(HUFs)%20involved%20in%20proprietary%20businesses%20or%20professions.%20It%20is%20suitable%20if%20you%20engage%20in%20a%20business%20or%20profession%20requiring%20bookkeeping%20or%20audit%2C%20are%20a%20director%20in%20a%20company%2C%20or%20have%20investments%20in%20unlisted%20equity%20shares%20during%20the%20financial%20year.%20It%20covers%20income%20from%20house%20property%2C%20salary%20or%20pension%2C%20other%20sources%2C%20and%20as%20a%20partner%20in%20a%20firm.%20If%20you%20don't%20fit%20ITR-1%2C%20ITR-2%2C%20or%20ITR-4%20criteria%2C%20ITR-3%20is%20the%20appropriate%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EITR-4%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20also%20known%20as%20Sugam%2C%20is%20a%20simplified%20Income%20Tax%20Return%20form%20suitable%20for%20residents%20who%20are%20individuals%2C%20Hindu%20Undivided%20Families%20(HUFs)%2C%20and%20partnership%20firms%20(excluding%20LLPs).%20It%20applies%20to%20those%20with%20specific%20income%20sources%2C%20including%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBusiness%20or%20professional%20income%20under%20presumptive%20taxation%20schemes%20(Sections%2044AD%20or%2044ADA).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIncome%20from%20one%20residential%20property%2C%20not%20exceeding%20Rs.%2050%20lakh%20(excluding%20carried%20forward%20losses).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESalary%20or%20pension%20income%20up%20to%20Rs.%2050%20lakh.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOther%20sources%20of%20income%20up%20to%20Rs.%2050%20lakh%20(excluding%20lottery%20and%20race-horse%20winnings).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFreelancers%20earning%20within%20these%20thresholds%20can%20opt%20for%20presumptive%20taxation%20if%20their%20gross%20receipts%20are%20under%20Rs.%2050%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EITR-5%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20a%20comprehensive%20Income%20Tax%20Return%20form%20for%20various%20entities%20such%20as%20firms%2C%20LLPs%2C%20AOPs%2C%20BOIs%2C%20AJPs%2C%20estates%2C%20business%20trusts%2C%20and%20investment%20funds%2C%20accommodating%20diverse%20business%20structures%20and%20legal%20entities%20under%20Indian%20tax%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EITR-6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20is%20the%20specific%20Income%20Tax%20Return%20form%20for%20companies%20under%20the%20Companies%20Act%202013%20or%20earlier%20versions%2C%20excluding%20those%20exempt%20under%20Section%2011%20for%20income%20from%20charitable%20or%20religious%20property.%20It%20ensures%20compliance%20with%20tax%20filing%20requirements%20for%20non-exempt%20corporate%20entities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EITR-7%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20an%20extensive%20income%20tax%20return%20form%20intended%20for%20specific%20entities%20mandated%20to%20file%20returns%20under%20sections%20139(4D)%2C%20139(4A)%2C%20139(4B)%2C%20139(4C)%2C%20139(4E)%2C%20and%20139(4F)%20of%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Act.%20This%20includes%20companies%2C%20political%20parties%20with%20taxable%20income%2C%20scientific%20research%20associations%2C%20news%20agencies%2C%20educational%20institutions%2C%20business%20trusts%2C%20and%20certain%20investment%20funds%20under%20Section%20115UB.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719060000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-08%2F62h9bcgg_income-tax-return-itr-unsplash_625x300_29_August_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fincome-tax-return-find-out-which-itr-form-is-required-for-your-income-tax-filing-5946257%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Filing%20your%20Income%20Tax%20Return%20(ITR)%20by%20July%2031%2C%202024%2C%20is%20mandatory%20in%20India%2C%20with%20a%20late%20fee%20for%20delays.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fincome-tax-return-find-out-which-itr-form-is-required-for-your-income-tax-filing-5946257%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fincome-tax-return-find-out-which-itr-form-is-required-for-your-income-tax-filing-5946257%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fincome-tax-return-find-out-which-itr-form-is-required-for-your-income-tax-filing-5946257%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20was%20raised%20to%20believe%20I%20should%20be%20generou