m%20%26quot%3Bexaggerated%20and%20biased%20allegations%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F06%2F21%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fhinduja-family-human-trafficking-trial.html%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20members%20were%20acquitted%20of%20more%20serious%20charge%20of%20human%20trafficking%2C%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20the%20workers%20had%20travelled%20to%20Switzerland%20willingly.%20But%2C%20they%20were%20convicted%20on%20other%20charges%20in%20a%20stunning%20verdict%20for%20the%20family%2C%20whose%20fortune%20is%20reportedly%20estimated%20at%2037%20billion%20pounds%20(%2447%20billion).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrakash%20Hinduja%2C%2078%2C%20and%20his%20wife%20Kamal%20Hinduja%2C%2075%2C%20each%20got%20four%20years%20and%20six%20months%2C%20while%20their%20son%20Ajay%2C%2056%2C%20and%20his%20wife%20Namrata%2C%2050%2C%20received%20four-year%20terms%2C%20the%20presiding%20judge%20in%20Geneva%20ruled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20family%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20said%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bappalled%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20ruling%20and%20filed%20an%20appeal%20in%20a%20higher%20court%20challenging%20the%20verdict%20finding%20them%20guilty%20of%20exploiting%20vulnerable%20domestic%20workers%20from%20India%20at%20their%20villa%20in%20Geneva.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20convicted%20of%20%26quot%3Busury%26quot%3B%20for%20having%20taken%20advantage%20of%20their%20vulnerable%20immigrant%20staff%20to%20pay%20them%20a%20pittance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20employees'%20inexperience%20was%20exploited%2C%26quot%3B%20judge%20Sabina%20Mascotto%20said%20in%20her%20judgement.%20%26quot%3BThey%20had%20little%20education%20or%20none%20at%20all%20and%20had%20no%20knowledge%20of%20their%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20defendants'%20motives%20were%20selfish%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20Hindujas%20were%20motivated%20%26quot%3Bby%20the%20desire%20for%20gain%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Spent%20More%20On%20Dog%20Than%20On%20Staff'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProsecutor%20accused%20the%20Hindujas%20of%20spending%20%26quot%3Bmore%20on%20their%20dog%20than%20on%20their%20domestic%20employees%26quot%3B.%20The%20family%20paid%20the%20household%20staff%20about%20325%20francs%20(%24363)%20a%20month%2C%20up%20to%2090%20percent%20less%20than%20the%20going%20rate%2C%20the%20judge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20had%20reached%20a%20confidential%20out-of-court%20settlement%20with%20the%20three%20employees%20who%20made%20the%20accusations%20against%20them%2C%20leading%20them%20to%20drop%20their%20legal%20action%2C%20said%20the%20defence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%2C%20the%20prosecution%20had%20decided%20to%20pursue%20the%20case%20due%20to%20the%20seriousness%20of%20the%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20verdict%2C%20the%20prosecutor%20requested%20an%20immediate%20detention%20order%20for%20Ajay%20and%20Namrata%20Hinduja%2C%20claiming%20a%20flight%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judged%20denied%20it%2C%20accepting%20the%20defence%20argument%20that%20the%20family%20had%20ties%20to%20Switzerland.%20It%20noted%20that%20Kamal%20Hinduja%20was%20hospitalised%20in%20Monaco%20and%20the%20three%20other%20family%20members%20were%20at%20her%20bedside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Employees%20Received%20Ample%20Benefits'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20not%20dealing%20with%20mistreated%20slaves%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20defence%20told%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20argued%20that%20the%20three%20employees%20received%20ample%20benefits%2C%20were%20not%20kept%20in%20isolation%20and%20were%20free%20to%20leave%20the%20villa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERomain%20Jordan%20had%20also%20pleaded%20for%20acquittal%2C%20claiming%20the%20prosecutors%20were%20aiming%20to%20make%20an%20example%20of%20the%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20argued%20the%20prosecution%20had%20failed%20to%20mention%20extra%20payments%20made%20to%20staff%20on%20top%20of%20their%20cash%20salaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20interests%20in%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20banking%20and%20healthcare%2C%20the%20Hinduja%20Group%20is%20present%20in%2038%20countries%20and%20employs%20around%20200%2C000%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719055800000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Ftg30klj_hindujas-afp_625x300_22_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Fhindujas-made-staff-sleep-in-windowless-basement-at-swiss-mansion-report-5945852%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Four%20members%20of%20Britain's%20richest%20family%2C%20the%20Hindujas%20have%20received%20jail%20sentences%20by%20a%20Swiss%20court%20on%20Friday%20for%20exploiting%20Indian%20staff%20at%20their%20Geneva%20mansion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Fhindujas-made-staff-sleep-in-windowless-basement-at-swiss-mansion-report-5945852%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Fhindujas-made-staff-sleep-in-windowless-basement-at-swiss-mansion-report-5945852%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findians-abroad%2Fhindujas-made-staff-sleep-in-windowless-basement-at-swiss-mansion-report-5945852%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20millennial%20couple%20who%20ditched%20van%20life%20to%20buy%20a%20%24150%2C000%20hoarder%20house%20said%20it's%20worth%20it.%20Take%20a%20look%20inside.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Drew%20and%20Becky%20Bidlen%20holding%20their%20daughter%20in%20front%20of%20their%20home%20(Left)%20and%20an%20interior%20shot%20of%20one%20of%20the%20rooms%20covered%20in%20clutter.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66719d75764df161125ab9e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3