rt-de-niro-has-used-surrogates-for-three-of-his-children-with-both-toukie-smith-and-grace-hightower-33%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESurrogacy%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20on%20the%20rise%20worldwide%2C%20with%20the%20global%20surrogacy%20market%20worth%20an%20estimated%20%2414%20billion%20in%202022%2C%20according%20to%20market%20research%20consultancy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gminsights.com%2Findustry-analysis%2Fsurrogacy-market%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Market%20Insights%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Traditional%20surrogacy%20is%20when%20a%20woman%20is%20artificially%20inseminated%2C%20but%20more%20common%20today%20is%20gestational%20surrogacy%2C%20in%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fivf-surrogacy-egg-donation-sisters-help-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIVF%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20used%20to%20place%20a%20fertilized%20embryo%20into%20a%20surrogate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20her%20friend%2C%20Wilkinson%20had%20also%20had%20easy%20pregnancies%20with%20her%20two%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20hate%20to%20say%20it%20because%20it%20sounds%20obnoxious%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20have%20morning%20sickness.%20I%20didn't%20get%20stretch%20marks.%20It%20was%20the%20epitome%20of%20perfect%20pregnancies%20with%20no%20issues%20whatsoever%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20decided%20she%20wanted%20to%20help%20others%20have%20children%2C%20she%20ended%20up%20going%20with%20the%20same%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnaomi-campbell-kids-after-50-via-surrogacy-motherhood-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurrogacy%3C%2Fa%3E%20agency%20her%20friend%20used%3A%20Circle.%20For%20her%20first%20surrogacy%20journey%2C%20she%20got%20matched%20with%20a%20single%20dad.%20She%20was%20paid%20%2422%2C500%20and%20delivered%20the%20baby%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20an%20incredible%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20remember%20being%20in%20the%20hospital%20saying%20to%20my%20husband%2C%20'I%20know%20this%20sounds%20crazy%2C%20but%20I%20know%20that%20I%20want%20to%20do%20this%20again.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Circle%20reached%20out%20to%20see%20if%20she'd%20be%20interested%20in%20going%20through%20the%20process%20again%2C%20she%20said%20%26quot%3Byes.%26quot%3B%20This%20time%2C%20she%20was%20matched%20with%20a%20gay%20couple%20from%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20second%20experience%20was%20also%20a%20little%20different%2C%20as%20this%20time%2C%20she%20was%20part%20of%20what's%20called%20a%20dual%20journey%20or%20a%20concurrent%20journey%2C%20where%20there%20are%20two%20separates%20surrogates%20hired%20to%20carry%20babies%20for%20the%20same%20set%20of%20intended%20parents.%20Though%20the%20couple%20contracted%20two%20surrogates%2C%20they%20staggered%20the%20pregnancies%20to%20not%20overlap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20understand%20wanting%20to%20build%20your%20family%20and%20wanting%20to%20have%20more%20than%20one%20child%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20surrogacy%20journeys%20can%20take%20a%20lot%20of%20time%2C%20sometimes%20two%20years%2C%20and%20so%20for%20some%20parents%2C%20it%20may%20make%20sense%20to%20do%20two%20at%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20time%2C%20Wilkinson%20delivered%20in%202016%20and%20was%20paid%20%2430%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20Wilkinson%20said%20the%20typical%20base%20pay%20for%20a%20first-time%20surrogate%20can%20be%20anywhere%20from%20%2435%2C000%20to%20%2450%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20intended%20parents%2C%20they%20can%20pay%20anywhere%20from%20around%20%24200%2C000%20or%20more%20to%20have%20a%20child%20via%20surrogacy.%20Other%20costs%20that%20go%20into%20the%20process%20include%20legal%20fees%20for%20contracts%2C%20clinical%20bills%2C%20and%20agency%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20price%20point%20of%20surrogacy%20can%20make%20it%20a%20luxury%2C%20Wilkinson%20said%20some%20people%20go%20to%20great%20lengths%20to%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20heard%20of%20intended%20parents%20that%20are%20taking%20out%20second%20mortgages%20on%20their%20house%20or%20just%20going%20through%20different%20avenues%20to%20afford%20surrogacy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilkinson%20said%20she%20found%20the%20surrogacy%20experience%20empowering%2C%20and%20now%20she's%20committed%20to%20helping%20other%20surrogates%20have%20fulfilling%20journeys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20deciding%20to%20become%20a%20surrogate%2C%20she%20said%20it%20really%20comes%20down%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhy.%26quot%3B%20For%20her%2C%20she%20said%20it%20goes%20back%20to%20her%20favorite%20aunt.%20As%20a%20kid%2C%20she%20always%20wondered%20why%20her%20aunt%20never%20had%20kids%20of%20her%20own.%20It%20wasn't%20until%20she%20got%20older%20that%20she%20realized%20her%20aunt%20had%20wanted%20kids%20but%20was%20unable%20to%20have%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20tons%20of%20people%20just%20like%20my%20aunt%20that%20are%20equally%20deserving%20and%20equally%20have%20that%20yearning%20to%20be%20a%20parent%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20I%20knew%20that%20I%20could%20help.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20news%20tip%20or%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20surrogacy%3F%20Were%20you%20an%20intended%20parent%20in%20a%20concurrent%20surrogacy%20journey%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Akvlamis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ekvlamis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurrogate-paid-22500-and-30000-twice-said-experience-was-empowering-2024-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719054242000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66749b2f423319f0c3723234%3Fformat%3D