3A%22Sunita%20Williams'%20Return%20From%20Space%20Delayed%20Due%20To%20Spacecraft%20Glitches%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20American%20space%20agency%20NASA%20has%20confirmed%20that%20the%20return%20of%20Indian%20origin%20astronaut%20Sunita%20Williams%20from%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20(ISS)%20has%20been%20further%20delayed%20and%20no%20new%20date%20has%20been%20set%20for%20her%20%26quot%3Bhappy%20landing%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20comes%20as%20the%20spacecraft%20in%20which%20she%20travelled%20to%20space%2C%20the%20Boeing%20Starliner%2C%20has%20been%20facing%20a%20series%20of%20glitches.%20Sunita%20Williams%20and%20her%20co-passenger%20Butch%20Wilmore%20are%20both%20safe%20on%20the%20ISS%20along%20with%20the%20seven%20other%20crew%20members%20who%20inhabit%20the%20%26quot%3Bmini-city%20in%20space%26quot%3B%20-%20the%20ISS.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERiding%20atop%20the%20Boeing%20Starliner%20on%20its%20maiden%20mission%2C%20Ms%20Williams%20reached%20the%20ISS%20on%20June%205%20on%20what%20was%20to%20be%20possibly%20a%2010-day%20mission%20but%20since%20then%20it%20has%20been%20extended%20twice%20thanks%20to%20issues%20with%20the%20small%20rockets%20that%20help%20the%20crew%20module%20return%20to%20Earth%2C%20and%20a%20series%20of%20Helium%20leaks%20that%20bedevil%20the%20Boeing%20Starliner%20on%20its%20first%20crewed%20flight.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20says%20the%20crew%20is%20not%20pressed%20for%20time%20to%20leave%20the%20station%20since%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20supplies%20in%20orbit%2C%20and%20the%20station's%20schedule%20is%20relatively%20open%20through%20mid-August.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20Ms%20Williams%20was%20to%20return%20potentially%20on%20June%2014%2C%20this%20was%20scrapped%20and%20a%20new%20date%20June%2026%20was%20set%20by%20NASA%2C%20this%20has%20also%20been%20postponed%20and%20a%20new%20date%20has%20not%20been%20announced%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNASA%20and%20Boeing%20leadership%20are%20adjusting%20the%20return%20to%20Earth%20of%20the%20Starliner%20Crew%20Flight%20Test%20spacecraft%20with%20agency%20astronauts.%20The%20move%20off%20Wednesday%2C%20June%2026%2C%20deconflicts%20Starliner's%20undocking%20and%20landing%20from%20a%20series%20of%20planned%20International%20Space%20Station%20spacewalks%20while%20allowing%20mission%20teams%20time%20to%20review%20propulsion%20system%20data%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFive%20of%20the%2028%20thrusters%20on%20the%20Boeing%20Starliner%20are%20having%20issues%20and%20there%20have%20been%20five%20Helium%20leaks%20on%20the%20space%20craft.%20Experts%20say%20a%20minimum%20of%2014%20thrusters%20are%20required%20for%20a%20safe%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoeing%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BStarliner%20has%20completed%2077%20of%20the%20original%2087%20flight-test%20objectives%2C%20with%20the%20remaining%2010%20will%20occur%20between%20undocking%20and%20landing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20says%20mission%20managers%20are%20evaluating%20future%20return%20opportunities%20following%20the%20station's%20two%20planned%20spacewalks%20on%20Monday%2C%20June%2024%2C%20and%20Tuesday%2C%20July%202.%20So%20it%20could%20well%20be%20nearly%20a%20month%20long%20stay%20for%20Ms%20Williams%20in%20space%20on%20her%20third%20mission%20to%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStarliner%20is%20performing%20well%20in%20orbit%20while%20docked%20to%20the%20space%20station%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Steve%20Stich%2C%20manager%20of%20NASA's%20Commercial%20Crew%20Program%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20strategically%20using%20the%20extra%20time%20to%20clear%20a%20path%20for%20some%20critical%20station%20activities%20while%20completing%20readiness%20for%20Butch%20and%20Suni's%20return%20on%20Starliner%20and%20gaining%20valuable%20insight%20into%20the%20system%20upgrades%20we%20will%20want%20to%20make%20for%20post-certification%20missions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoeing%20has%20faced%20several%20hiccups%20in%20the%20Starliner%20development%20and%20initially%20it%20was%20to%20have%20completed%20this%20with%20a%20%244.2%20billion%20contract%20but%20has%20now%20spent%20a%20total%20of%20about%20%24%205.7%20billion%20and%20the%20going%20is%20still%20uphill%20as%20the%20mission%20remains%20incomplete.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20wanted%20a%20second%20alternative%20to%20SpaceX's%20Crew%20Dragon%20and%20hence%20Boeing%20Starliner%20was%20being%20pushed%20through.%20Boeing%20is%20going%20through%20a%20bad%20patch%20in%20general%20and%20its%20aviation%20and%20aircraft%20business%20has%20also%20been%20stumbling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20says%20Wilmore%20and%20Williams%20remain%20integrated%20with%20the%20Expedition%2071%20crew%2C%20assisting%20with%20station%20operations%20as%20needed%20and%20completing%20add-on%20in-flight%20objectives%20for%20NASA%20certification%20of%20Starliner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Williams%20is%20a%20qualified%20navy%20test%20pilot%20she%20had%20flown%20twice%20earlier%20to%20space%20in%202006%20and%202012%20and%20according%20to%20data%20from%20NASA%2C%20before%20this%20Starliner%20mission%20Sunita%20has%20already%20spent%20a%20cumulative%20total%20of%20322%20days%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20seven%20space%20walks%20totalling%2050%20hours%20and%2040%20minutes%2C%20Sunita%20held%20the%20record%20for%20total%20cumulative%20spacewalk%20time%20by%20a%20female%20astronaut%20but%20that%20has%20since%20been%20overtaken%20by%20Peggy%20Whitson%20with%2010%20spacewalks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMs%20Williams%20has%20helped%20design%20the%20Boeing%20Starliner%20so%20she%20should%20be%20familiar%20with%20all%20its%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESuch%20Delays%20Not%20Unforeseen%20on%20Maiden%20Missions%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20taking%20our%20time%20and%20following%20our%20standard%20mission%20management%20team%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Stich.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20letting%20the%20data%20drive%20our%20decision%20making%20relative%20to%20managing%20the%20small%20helium%20system%20leaks%20and%20thruster%20performance%20we%20observed%20during%20rendezvous%20and%20docking.%20Additionally%2C%20given%20the%20duration%20of%20the%20mission%2C%20it%20is%20appropriate%20for%20us%20to%20complete%20an%20agency-level%20review%2C%20similar%20to%20what%20was%20done%20ahead%20of%20the%20NASA's%20SpaceX%20Demo-2%20return%20after%20two%20months%20on%20orbit%2C%20to%20document%20the%20agency's%20formal%20acceptance%20on%20proceeding%20as%20planned.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20space%20fairing%20community%20prays%20for%20the%20safe%20return%20of%20Ms%20Williams%20and%20Mr%20Wilmore%2C%20but%20it%20could%20be%20embarrassing%20for%20Boeing%20if%20SpaceX's%20Crew%20Dragon%20were%20to%20be%20used%20to%20rescue%20the%20astronauts%20stuck%20at%20the%20space%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20crew's%20feedback%20has%20been%20overwhelmingly%20positive%2C%20and%20they%20know%20that%20every%20bit%20of%20learning%20we%20do%20on%20the%20Crew%20Flight%20Test%20will%20improve%20and%20sharpen%20our%20experience%20for%20future%20crews%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mark%20Nappi%2C%20vice%20president%20and%20program%20manager%2C%20Boeing's%20Starliner%20Program.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719044460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2F8pjhfdeo_sunita-williams_625x300_07_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsunita-williams-return-from-space-delayed-due-to-spacecraft-glitches-5944651%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20American%20space%20agency%20NASA%20has%20confirmed%20that%20the%20return%20of%20the%20Indian%20origin%20astronaut%20Sunita%20Williams%20from%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20(ISS)%20has%20been%20further%20delayed%20and%20no%20new%20date%20has%20been%20set%20for%20her%20%26quot%3Bhappy%20landing%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canoni